The paper presents a Bayesian nonparametric mixed membership model for text data, which is a common topic in machine learning and natural language processing. The use of Dirichlet processes and variational Bayes also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
